Trade Marketing Manager Job (Consumer Goods), Jakarta, Indonesia  -
Trade Marketing Manager Job (Consumer Goods), Jakarta, Indonesia
Responsibilities
Monroe Consulting Group is recruiting on behalf of one of the world’s leading consumer goods and personal care companies. Our respected client is seeking a sales and marketing professional, preferably with experience working in a multinational consumer goods or pharmaceutical company, for the job of Trade Marketing Manager, to be based in Jakarta, Indonesia. The winning candidate will report directly to the Head of Trade Marketing. Key job responsibilities will include: Plays a key role within the Country Sales team, driving excellence in store (4P) execution across key customers/key accountFocusing on building expert knowledge in our key categories and sharing this with the customer in order to build long-term partnerships and increase profit and salesLeads within the country the development and implementation of category management strategies, this will focus on increasing the company’s in store presence in our categories, strengthening our brands, optimizing product assortment, and promotional strategyThe role holder has constant interaction with the Marketing and the Sales teamExternally s/he interacts with the Wholesalers, Distributors and the Key AccountsDelivery of category and  channel P&L as per company objectivesDeveloping a 4P/3D category and channel master plan with distinct KPIs and ROIs in line with the marketing master plan to deliver the annual P&L. The plan is to be developed in consultation with various stake holders like marketing/field sales. The annual master plan is then to be split into monthly deliverablesDevelop NPD/EPD launch plans for one's own category/channelDevelop channel specific and category specific POSM in line with the guidelines at minimum cost.Develop allocation of consumer promos in line with the strategic intentPlanning for tactical response in case of competitive threats or opportunitiesAssist the sales team in improving their efficiency by equipping them with tools/selling stories and  developing training modules for the sameLocalize global 4P strategies and principles; convert global success models into local success modelsDesigning KPIs for various players like DBSRs/SPGs/RB Field force on efficiencyMonitoring the performance of initiatives in Sales Master Plan against the KPIs, course correcting for deviations.Trade investment  to be in line with the financial planDevelop effective communication packages on a monthly/quarterly basis so as to facilitate the sales team to communicate the various trade programs and consumer promos with the key beneficiaries in the best possible mannerIdentification of key sales issues and taking the right action promptlyContinuously seeking opportunities to grow the business in sync with the market plan Job Requirements  Bachelor’s degree (minimum) in sales, marketing, or business administration with a Master degree in business administration preferredAt least 4-5 Years of mandatory field experience + existing key accounts, trade marketing, brand management experience with FMCG or pharmaceutical companyStrong knowledge of field sales and trade marketingResults oriented, entrepreneurial and self-motivatedTenacious and resilient, driven to achieve even when faced with obstaclesLeadership and interpersonal skills capable of building strong working relationships and influencing and customers and internal teamsCreative and innovative in designing schemesSound commercial understanding of business issues, opportunitiesClear understanding of sales and marketing strategy and planning issuesStrong analytical skills with ability to develop strategies, tactics and measurable implementationAble to speak fluently in English All applications will be treated in the strictest of confidence. If you are a suitable match for this position please send your application to consumer@monroeconsulting.com
